[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring dependencies for instrumentation**\n\nI'm considering whether the extra dependency for opentelemetry-sdk-testing is necessary. It seems like it might not be allowed, but I could probably manage without it. The RestTemplate instrumentation class seems important for adding interceptors and asserting requests contain the traceparent header with MockRestServiceServer. \n\nI'll set up MockRestServiceServer with RestTemplate and check the trace headers. I'll make sure the interceptor creates spans and injects them properly too. There are some questions about configuring RestTemplateBuilder in a non-web Boot app, but it looks like Spring’s auto-config should cover it.\n\n**Testing controller/server instrumentation**\n\nI'm considering if I can test controller/server instrumentation with MockMvc. It might work to define a controller in a non-web environment and use MockMvc. However, server instrumentation might require some additional setup, like instrumenting HandlerMapping, which could be tricky without an exporter. \n\nI could create a `@RestController` and start SpringApplication on a random port using TestRestTemplate, but that might feel too heavy. Instead, I’ll need to ensure all auto-config resources are loaded correctly. Running tests in native mode without Spring AOT hints seems problematic due to the dynamic reflection involved.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c1b8044c57f890e016a3e8eb79698819684af5075f77b2623\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPo7XG7k6B_KeEzzXtGI4LqLoMC4kfO5Gcg-jX-qqrGWDoH2AVrWecQjGxQSX0V3Lai1H9A3MCnKfWdXK5QcQ6puOhgvelmrORUgID2jakun_uenADCGCea4hVEhnXpLqGuTSp7aPzOkElwxeM2qPU9N2Itv79gnDnV4xmjHiUl2rVacm68ZGxCHuVn3zWHbrVI6IsqkgrBGiDFCu3bmEdoAWlleP_yaY93wtIijqKaUiDJnWHoJnzoxXSJG1DoeLGlCs6PQlikhcvxj-k1Z9DhLCCK07Avx2RKqZWCajPRfbq5b8OFX5cMlRSsfx42YNKKXGgE1vvlUuPgvbqZpNoG90aw7Hq-31SeqVs3u-hdSlYxh